-- Aquarius, Howden, SacOil and Tongaat May Move: South Africa Stocks Preview
-- Renee Bonorchis
-- 2010-07-27T05:44:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/aquarius-howden-sacoil-and-tongaat-may-move-south-africa-stocks-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a
fifth day, climbing 74.83, or 0.3 percent, to 28,499 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg, the highest since May 3.  
 Aquarius Platinum Ltd.  (AQP SJ): The fourth-largest
producer of the metal said a fatal accident at its Marikana mine
in South Africa cut July production by 40 percent, or 4,400
ounces of platinum, palladium, rhodium and gold. New safety
measures will boost costs by 5 percent, it said. Shares in the
company rose 14 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 31.74 rand.  
 Howden Africa Holdings Ltd.  (HWN SJ): The maker of
equipment to handle air, gas and liquids said earnings per share
from continuing operations in the six months through June will
be between 35 cents and 50 cents, compared with earnings of
74.32 cents a year earlier. Shares in Howden gained 30 cents, or
2.5 percent, to 12.30 rand.  
 Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.  (KIO SJ): The Anglo American Plc unit
may consider “value sharing” if it wins arbitration over a
disputed minority stake in mining rights at its Sishen mine in
South Africa, Business Day reported, citing an unidentified
company spokesman.  
 South Africa will make a decision on the rights “within
the next week,” Department of Minerals Director General  Sandile Nogxina  said separately. Kumba was unchanged at 368 rand.  
 MTN Group Ltd.  (MTN SJ): Africa’s largest mobile operator
was upgraded to “equal weight” at Morgan Stanley from
“underweight”. MTN fell 55 cents, or 0.5 percent, to 117.95
rand.  
 SacOil Holdings Ltd.  (SCL SJ) The oil explorer said it has
reorganized the way a transaction regarding oil concessions in
the Democratic Republic of Congo will be carried out and will
pay 439.9 million rand ($60 million) in stock to secure control
of an oil concession near Lake Albert. Sacoil fell 4 cents, or
5.4 percent, to 70 cents.  
 Tongaat Hulett Ltd.  (TON SJ): The sugar company hosts its
annual general meeting of shareholders. Tongaat gained 47 cents,
or 0.4 percent, to 108 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) climbed 0.3 percent to
$19.62. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 0.3 percent to
$40.08. BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) gained 0.4 percent to $60.93.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) dropped 0.7 percent to $4.18. Gold
Fields Ltd. (GFI US) declined 0.3 percent to $13.07. Harmony
Gold Mining Co. (HMY US) lost 0.1 percent to $10.01. Impala
Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US) jumped 3 percent to $27.96. Sappi
Ltd. (SPP US) climbed 3.1 percent to $4.68. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US)
increased 1.4 percent to $40.01.  
